{
  "stem": "7598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they told us that we would be the last car that would go through that evening.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They would close the frontier at 7:00 but that the next morning they would reopen it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "My mother suggested that my brother and I should stay with my uncle and aunt, and she would go back and fetch my father.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It may sound a bit strange that a mother leaves her children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And this is where I have to fill in a very, very important part of my parents' life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "My father was forced to fight against Belgium and France and England in 1914 because he was a Pole under the Austrian empire.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And although he relented for a long time, eventually, in 1917-- he didn't tell-- he never told me this story.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "My mother told me this after he died.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "He actually had to fight for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "He tried everything to avoid it, including sleeping on straw.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And he got asthma, which was with him all his life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But, nevertheless, he eventually had to fight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Fight-- he didn't fight, but he had to work in an office in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Consequently, when he returned in Belgium, to Belgium after the war and applied for naturalization papers in the '20s, he was refused naturalization because he had been an enemy alien.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "At that point, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Poland-- having a Polish passport was not a, a very welcome thing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "So my father became a stateless person.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "He had a stateless passport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Although my brother and I were born in Belgium, we weren't really considered Belgian because our Father was Polish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Therefore, we had stateless paper.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "My mother was born in Belgium with Belgian paper.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "When she arrived at the frontier, she didn't show our stateless paper.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
